- F1 score is a measure of a model's accuracy on a specific task, calculated as the harmonic mean of precision and recall; 
- Cumulative F1 score refers to the running sum of F1 scores over time, providing insight into the overall model performance trend; 
- Average F1 score is the mean of F1 scores across multiple processes or tasks, offering a general idea of the model's performance; 
- Corrective actions are steps taken to address identified issues or problems, usually resulting from audit findings; 
- Preventive actions are proactive steps taken to prevent issues or problems from occurring in the first place.

sql:
SELECT action_description, actionDate
FROM corrective_actions
WHERE action_status = 'completed';
